## 4. External API Endpoint Specification

All external APIs are accessed via the backend (FastAPI). The frontend NEVER calls external APIs directly. API keys are stored as environment variables server-side.

### 4.1 ASYCUDA Endpoints

```
Base URL:  [ASYCUDA_BASE_URL] (env var)
Auth:      X-API-Key: [ASYCUDA_API_KEY] (env var)

GET /manifest/{port_code}/{year}/{r_number}
Response: {
  "status": "found" | "not_found" | "not_assessed" | "locked" | "system_error",
  "vessel_name": string,
  "voyage_number": string,
  "date_of_arrival": string,
  "bl_number": string,
  "gross_weight": number,
  "package_code": string,
  "packs_number": number,
  "exporter": string,
  "consignee": string,
  "carrier": string,
  "form_locked_by": string | null,
  "ff_account_code": string,
  "consignee_code": string
}

GET /account/validate/{ff_code}/{consignee_code}
Response: {
  "compatible": boolean,
  "balance_sufficient": boolean,
  "current_balance": number
}
```

### 4.2 Tradian Endpoints

```
Base URL:  [TRADIAN_BASE_URL] (env var)
Auth:      X-API-Key: [TRADIAN_API_KEY] (env var)

GET /bl/{bl_number}
Response: {
  "found": boolean,
  "bl_number": string,
