## 8. Fine Calculation Logic

```python
def calculate_fine(service_types: list, amendment_types: list) -> int:
    fine = 0
    
    # Late manifest: MVR 3,000 (fixed, additive)
    if "late_manifest" in service_types:
        fine += 3000
    
    # Amendment fine (take highest tier only)
    tier_1_fields = {"exporter", "notify_party", "place_of_discharge", "final_destination"}
    tier_2_fields = {"consignee", "gross_weight", "container_number", "goods_description",
                     "bl_awb_split", "bl_awb_number", "place_of_loading", "no_of_packages",
                     "seal_number", "volume"}
    
    amended = set(amendment_types)
    
    if amended & tier_2_fields:
        fine += 1000
    elif amended & tier_1_fields:
        fine += 500
    
    return fine
```

